<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you use a Zend_Service class which uses the Basic auth capabilities of the Zend_Http_Client prior to using Zend_Service_Amazon_S3, then you can end up two conflicting Authorization headers in the request to S3.  In order to fix this, the S3 class could run $client-&gt;setAuth(FALSE) just after $client-&gt;resetParameters().  Alternatively, Zend_Http_Client::resetParameters could reset $this-&gt;auth to null.</p>

    </div>
</div>

